name: Tax Officer A
description:
A tax official with the verification paper in his hand sat in the house waiting for the verification.
"Why is the inspection so slow today? I still rushed to the post house to accompany my friends to buy drunk. Isn't it just signing to get something? Is it necessary to be so slow? Bureaucracy kills people." From an ordinary middle-aged person. Grassroots officials.

chinese.name: 税务官甲
chinese.description:
一位手里拿着核验纸张的税务官，坐在屋内等待查验。
“今日的查验为何如此缓慢？我这边可还赶着去驿馆陪友人买醉哪。不就是签个字拿点东西吗，有必要这么磨蹭？官僚主义害死人啊。”来自普通的中年基层官员。

name: The Pedestrian
description:
A pedestrian following the shopkeeper seems to be familiar with this hawking scene.
"I didn't expect that the shopkeeper's uncle is so old, and the years are making people old. But the craftsmanship of this board is still so crisp and beautiful, is there no apprentice to inherit this craft?"

chinese.name: 行人
chinese.description:
一位跟随在货郎身后的行人，似是对这叫卖场景司空见惯。
“没想到货郎阿叔年纪这么大了，岁月催人老啊。不过这打板的手艺还是那么地清脆漂亮，难道就没有个徒弟继承这手艺吗？”

name: Boatman A
description: The water flow suddenly reversed, causing the boat to shake violently. The boatman standing on the top of the boat staggered and almost fell. The boat in front was fighting for danger. No one could take care of this. In addition, the current was rushing, if you accidentally fell at this time. In the water, I'm afraid no one will come over and pull himself.

chinese.name: 船工甲
chinese.description: 水流突然倒转，使得船剧烈晃动，站在船顶的船工打了个踉跄，差点摔倒，前面的船正在抢险，没有人能顾及到这里，再加上水流湍急，若是自己在此时不慎跌入水中，恐怕不会有谁过来拉自己一把。

name: The Restaurant Owner
description: The owner of this wharf restaurant is using a long rod to adjust the position of the colored forging. These colored forgings have added some lively atmosphere to the shop. Even the ancients thousands of years ago have realized that the decoration of the facade is important for the business in the store. importance.

chinese.name: 饭店店主
chinese.description: 这家码头饭馆的店主正在用一顶长杆调整彩锻位置，这几条彩锻为店铺增加了些热闹的气氛，即便是数千年前的古人，也已经意识到了门面装点对于店内生意的重要性。

name: The Fortune-Telling Customer
description: A guest who patronized the fortune-telling booth. Dressed in white, he leaned slightly on the fortune-telling booth, and his expression was a little melancholy. He seemed to be puzzled about his own destiny or his present, and he urgently needed an expert to guide him.

chinese.name: 测命事主
chinese.description: 一位光顾了神算摊子的客人。他身着白衣，微微俯身趴在算命摊上，面色有些忧郁，似乎对自己的命运或是自己的现在感到疑惑，急需有高人指点逢凶化吉。

name: The Director
description: An old man who looked like a doctor was bragging to passersby about how powerful his plaster was"My plaster is a secret recipe handed down by my ancestors. I made the decision today to be sorry for my ancestors and sell it to those who are destined among you.".

chinese.name: 郎中
chinese.description:
一个像是郎中的老者，在向路过的行人们吹嘘他的膏药有多么厉害。
“我这帖膏药，可是老祖宗传下来的秘方，我今天做出了对不起祖宗的决定，把它卖给你们当中的有缘人。”

name: The Passing-By Wooden-Luggage Porter
description:
A pedestrian carrying two wooden boxes on a pole, judging from the arc of the pole, the two boxes may not weigh much, but they don't know what they are inside.
"This literati is also hypocritical. A little bit of goods can't be carried by a horse directly. But I can make a few glasses of wine."

chinese.name: 挑担行人
chinese.description:
一位用扁担挑着两个木箱的行人，从扁担的弧度来看这两只箱子或许无甚重量，只是不知里面当是何物。
“这文人也是矫情，些许点货物就不能直接让马扛着。不过我倒是可以借此赚几杯酒钱。”

name: The Vendor
description:
A hawker holding a portable stand, looking around for a stall to support the stall.
"The wine-carrying carts are walking in a hurry. It's better to set up a stall in another place. It's not worth it to be knocked down.

chinese.name: 卖货小贩
chinese.description:
一位手持便携式支架，四处寻觅摊位以支起货摊的小贩。
“这运酒的车马走得真是急，还是换个地方摆摊得好，被撞倒可就不值当了。”

name: The Traveler on The Bridge
description: A tourist passing by the bridge pointed to the passenger ship in the distance in a panic. He didn't know what to do. There was a passenger ship approaching in the distance. Behind him, a large ship was rushing, and its mast almost ran into it. The bridge.

chinese.name: 桥上游客
chinese.description: 一个路过这座桥的游客，他惊慌的指着远方的客船，不知道如何是好，远方正有一艘客船驶来，而自己的身后，一艘大船正在抢险，它的桅杆差一点就撞上了桥梁。

name: Carter C
description: The truck cover is a large-character screen written by the deposed old party. Inside the truck are collections of works and books by Sansu, Qin Guan, and Huang Tingjian. The truckmen were ordered by their owners to push them to the suburbs and burn them. If they were literate, would they? Choose to hide some of these precious books?

chinese.name: 车夫丙
chinese.description: 货车盖布是废黜旧党书写的大字屏风，车内装着的是三苏、秦观、黄庭坚的文集、书籍，车夫们奉主人之命将推其去郊外焚毁，要是他们识字的话，会不会选择把这些珍贵的书籍藏起来一些呢？

name: Wine-Carrying Solider A
description:
A drunkard soldier who seemed to drink a lot, stood aside drunkly watching his colleagues adjust their bows and arrows.
"Oh, Brother Sun, are you still drinking? It's all three barrels down, and there are eight barrels together. If we drink it again, we are still out of luck? Hey, who told you that you are dizzy. Oh, I have to shoot arrows. These days are getting more and more interesting. Hi, anyway, new wine is coming soon, and it’s not too late to ship."

chinese.name: 运酒军卒甲
chinese.description:
一个看起来喝得不少的运酒军卒，站在一边醉眼朦胧地看同僚调试弓箭。
“哟，孙哥，还喝呢？这可都三桶下去了，拢共就八桶，再喝下去咱们还运不运了？嗨，谁和你说头晕啊。嚯，还要射箭呢，这日子是越来越又意思了。嗨，反正就快有新酒来了，到时候再运也不迟。”

name: A Passer-By with a Burden
description:
A bearer who almost came across misfortune, dodges aside when he sees the drunk soldiers.
"Good guy, this car is really reckless. But if I also have a donkey cart, I don't have to carry this broken pole every day."

chinese.name: 挑担的路人
chinese.description:
一位差点路遇飞来横祸的挑担者，在看到醉醺醺的士卒时连忙躲闪到了一边。
“好家伙，这车可真莽撞。不过要是我也有辆驴车，就不用天天挑着这破扁担了。”

name: The Waiting Coachman
description: A groom holding a rein. He was boring and leaning on the side of the post, and there was no entertainment, and he didn't dare to leave here directly, and even the horse was so bored that he started to ring his nose, but the officer who was supposed to leave early in the morning was late, and he has not seen anyone.

chinese.name: 马夫
chinese.description: 一名手持缰绳的马夫。他百无聊赖倚靠在驿站旁边，又没有什么娱乐活动，又不敢直接离开这里，而连马都无聊得开始打响鼻，但应该在清早出发的差官却迟迟不来，至今不见人影。

name: Sculling Boatman B
description: Several boatmen were divided into two groups, left and right, and shook the big scull. The boatmen’s hard work and optimism are vividly remembered. It seems that they can hear rhythmic horns. It is quite difficult to shake such a big scull, but these boatmen still Didn't find it difficult.

chinese.name: 摇橹船夫乙
chinese.description: 数个船夫分左右两组奋力摇着大橹驶向前方，船工们的辛劳和乐观历历在目，似乎能听到有节奏的号子声，摇动这样的大橹相当费力，但这些船夫们还没有觉得多么困难。

name: The Restaurant Customer
description:
An alcoholic who eats happily with his companions, or a alcoholic who sips on the stilts may be a close friend.
"I really didn't drink enough for a thousand cups, but you, it must be enough. Isn't this Tokyo? Xiao Er! Bring him a good wine, which is my favorite."

chinese.name: 食客
chinese.description:
一位与同伴欢畅共食的酒客，与倚栏痛饮的酒客或许是至交好友。
“千杯我的确是没喝够，但你呀，肯定是够了。这儿不就是东京吗？小二！给他拿上好的美酒，就是我最爱的那个。”

name: Restaurant Guest B
description:
Business in this tea shop is booming, and the shop assistants are busy cleaning up. There is an endless stream of people who come to eat here, and a few guests are waiting for their refreshments to be served.
"With so many people coming to this shop, refreshments must not be wrong, so that I am also a member of the upper class."

chinese.name: 食客乙
chinese.description:
这家茶肆生意正旺，店铺伙计正忙着收拾，来此处就餐的人络绎不绝，几个客人正在等待着他们的茶点端上来。
“这么多人来这家店，茶点一定错不了，这样我也是上流的一员了。”

name: Servant B
description:
At the entrance of the tea shop, a guest slowly climbed up the back of the donkey. Xu Shi had just finished eating and planned to ride the donkey home. His servants were asking him to ride the donkey.
"Master, you drank too much again, come, I will help you on the donkey."

chinese.name: 侍从乙
chinese.description:
茶肆门口有客人缓慢地往驴背上爬，许是刚吃完饭，打算骑驴回家，他的仆从们正在招呼他骑上驴。
“老爷您又喝多了，来，我扶您上驴。”

traits.value: Sky blue color matching short sleeves

name: Chatting Teahouse Guest B
description:
In a tea shop by the Bian River, a few tea customers are gathering together, drinking tea and chatting, very comfortable.
"This tea is originally produced in Bianjing, and it is several times more expensive than that from other places."

chinese.name: 闲聊茶客乙
chinese.description:
在汴河边的一家茶坊里，几个茶客正聚在一起，一边饮茶，一边闲聊，十分惬意。
“这茶叶可是汴京原产的，比外地的要贵上好几倍呢。”

name: The Bellman
description:
A watchman who was startled by the sound of the quarrel downstairs temporarily put down his work and looked downstairs to watch the excitement.
"The thoughts of the sir, we ordinary people really don't understand. During the day, we collect taxes on those coachmen as we please, and in the evening I want to call the watch on time. Although there are no culprits at night, the days are good. Let's go to sleep first. , I have to work at night."

chinese.name: 更夫
chinese.description:
一个被楼下吵架之声惊动了的更夫，暂时放下了手里的活计，探头向楼下看热闹。
“官老爷的心思，我们这些老百姓真是想不明白。白天对那些车夫随心所欲地收税，晚上又要我准时准点地打更。虽说现在夜晚也不见有贼人了，日子倒是不错。还是先睡罢，晚上还得做工。”

name: The Director
description: An old man who looked like a doctor was bragging to passersby about how powerful his plaster was"My plaster is a secret recipe handed down by my ancestors. I made the decision today to be sorry for my ancestors and sell it to those who are destined among you.".

chinese.name: 郎中
chinese.description:
一个像是郎中的老者，在向路过的行人们吹嘘他的膏药有多么厉害。
“我这帖膏药，可是老祖宗传下来的秘方，我今天做出了对不起祖宗的决定，把它卖给你们当中的有缘人。”

name: A Father and A Son
description: Father, who is shopping with his children, is asking a hawker about the hand-made toys he has made. Although I really can’t see the fun of such gadgets, as long as the children can be happy, it will be fine. .

chinese.name: 一对父子
chinese.description: 带着孩子一起逛街的父亲，正在向一个小贩询问关于他出手的手制玩具，虽然说实在是看不出来这样的小玩意到底有什么好玩的，但只要小孩子能开心，怎么样都好了。

name: The Fortune-Telling Customer
description: A guest who patronized the fortune-telling booth. Dressed in white, he leaned slightly on the fortune-telling booth, and his expression was a little melancholy. He seemed to be puzzled about his own destiny or his present, and he urgently needed an expert to guide him.

chinese.name: 测命事主
chinese.description: 一位光顾了神算摊子的客人。他身着白衣，微微俯身趴在算命摊上，面色有些忧郁，似乎对自己的命运或是自己的现在感到疑惑，急需有高人指点逢凶化吉。

name: Chatting Teahouse Guest, A
description:
In a tea shop by the Bian River, a few tea customers are gathering together, drinking tea and chatting, very comfortable.
"People nowadays care about buying wine and eating, how can we taste tea in a tea shop so elegantly as a few of us."

chinese.name: 闲聊茶客甲
chinese.description:
在汴河边的一家茶坊里，几个茶客正聚在一起，一边饮茶，一边闲聊，十分惬意。
“现在的人净顾着买酒吃，哪像我们几个这么高雅地在茶铺品茶。”

name: Bystander D
description: When the shipwreck was about to happen, the spectators at the bridge head pointed, or exclaimed, enclosing the right side guardrail of the arch bridge, and several people tried to rescue them by crossing the railings. In fact, in this case, everyone is the same. In a panic, no one can tell whether they are helping or adding chaos.

chinese.name: 看客丁
chinese.description: 船难将发之时，桥头的看客或指指点点，或惊呼不已，把拱桥的右侧护栏围得水泄不通，有几个人越过栏杆企图施救，其实，这种情况下，所有人都是慌张的，他们是在帮忙，还是在添乱，没人分得清楚。

name: Idle Soldier D
description:
A group of soldiers on official business, but they are not mindful of their tasks, they just slouchy gathering outside the yamen, or sitting or lying down waiting for the officer to appear.
"Continue to sleep, keep on sleeping. If you don't get enough sleep, there is no strength to hurry."

chinese.name: 懒散士卒丁
chinese.description:
一群公务在身的士卒，但他们对于自己的任务并不上心，只是懒懒散散地聚在衙门外，或坐或躺地等待着长官出现。
“继续睡继续睡，不睡饱哪有力气赶路。”

name: The House Horse-Leading Servant
description: A servant holding a horse's head and waiting on the side. This horse may be the mount of the scribe next to him. It has nothing to do with the servant. The high-ranking person can stay away from the ground, while the toiler needs to provide strength.

chinese.name: 牵马家仆
chinese.description: 一位牵着马头等候在旁侧的仆人，这马或许是旁边那位文士的坐骑，和仆人没有什么关联，高位者可以足不沾地，而劳苦人需要提供力气。

name: The Delivery Boaters
description: Shipmen employed by smugglers, although the court built official warehouses along the Bianhe River, all the grains will be transported to private warehouses in the deep alleys of the grain merchants after they are unloaded. The price will be determined by the hearts of these smugglers.

chinese.name: 送货船工
chinese.description: 受雇于走私商贩的船工，朝廷虽沿汴河建官仓，但这些粮食卸下后都将被运往粮商深巷里的私仓，不出意外的话，等到收成不好的时节，粮食的价格将由这些走私商的一己之心而决定。

name: The Store Owner
description: This is a shop that sells paper horses for ghost artifacts. The vertical sign on one side of the door says "Wang's paper horse", and on the other side is a stack of paper horses. Around the Ching Ming Festival, the business of this shop will be very high. Hot, but now, most people choose to go around.

chinese.name: 店主
chinese.description: 这是家卖冥器纸马的店，门一侧的竖牌上写着"王家纸马"四字，另侧摆放着一叠做好的纸马，清明节前后，这家店的生意会非常火爆，但现在，大多数人都会选择绕着走。

name: Restaurant Guest A
description:
Business in this tea shop is booming, and the shop assistants are busy cleaning up. There is an endless stream of people who come to eat here, and several guests are waiting for their refreshments to be served.
"That person is already eating, why haven't the refreshments I ordered come up yet?"

chinese.name: 食客甲
chinese.description:
这家茶肆生意正旺，店铺伙计正忙着收拾，来此处就餐的人络绎不绝，几个客人正在等待着他们的茶点端上来。
“那人都吃撑了，我点的茶点为什么还没上来？”

name: Bystander D
description: When the shipwreck was about to happen, the spectators at the bridge head pointed, or exclaimed, enclosing the right side guardrail of the arch bridge, and several people tried to rescue them by crossing the railings. In fact, in this case, everyone is the same. In a panic, no one can tell whether they are helping or adding chaos.

chinese.name: 看客丁
chinese.description: 船难将发之时，桥头的看客或指指点点，或惊呼不已，把拱桥的右侧护栏围得水泄不通，有几个人越过栏杆企图施救，其实，这种情况下，所有人都是慌张的，他们是在帮忙，还是在添乱，没人分得清楚。

name: The Cake Stand Owner
description: A bakery owner who is introducing his newly-baked biscuits to his guests. Guest officer, our roasted duck, roasted young chicken, roasted goose sauce, chicken, bacon, Songhua tripe, bacon, sausage, assorted Supan, smoked chicken tripe-it doesn’t have any, but we have a new hot cake. How about a piece?

chinese.name: 饼铺老板
chinese.description: 一位正在向客人介绍自家新出炉胡饼的饼铺老板。客官，我们这烧花鸭烧雏鸡烧子鹅酱鸡腊肉松花小肚腊肉香肠什锦苏盘熏鸡白肚——它都没有，但我们有新出炉的热饼，来一块如何？

name: The Following Porter
description: A porter who followed the owner who had just arrived in Bianjing, as can be seen from the degree of bending of the pole, the luggage he was carrying was really uncomfortable, so that he was obviously slowed by a certain distance.

chinese.name: 挑夫
chinese.description: 一位跟随在刚到汴京的主人身后的挑夫，由扁担的弯曲程度看得出来，他所背负的行李是真的很不让人轻松，以至于使他明显地慢了一段距离。

name: Idle Soldier D
description:
A group of soldiers on official business, but they are not mindful of their tasks, they just slouchy gathering outside the yamen, or sitting or lying down waiting for the officer to appear.
"Continue to sleep, keep on sleeping. If you don't get enough sleep, there is no strength to hurry."

chinese.name: 懒散士卒丁
chinese.description:
一群公务在身的士卒，但他们对于自己的任务并不上心，只是懒懒散散地聚在衙门外，或坐或躺地等待着长官出现。
“继续睡继续睡，不睡饱哪有力气赶路。”

name: The Walking-By Porter
description: For passers-by passing by, the newly opened restaurant by the pier attracted his attention, but did not stop him. A store with gorgeous decorations like this must be something you can't afford to patronize.

chinese.name: 行路挑夫
chinese.description: 路过此地的行路人，码头边新开的饭馆吸引了他的眼光，却并没有让他停下脚步，像这样装潢华丽的门店，相必是自己这种扁担客光顾不起的吧。

name: Warning Boatman A
description: Seeing that the big ship is in distress, the boatmen standing on the tops of the boats moored on both sides of the canal are giving out loud warnings, in case the bow or stern of the passenger ship will accidentally collide when adjusting the direction. If two ships of this kind of draught collide Together, the consequences will be disastrous.

chinese.name: 示警船工甲
chinese.description: 眼看大船遇险，运河两岸停泊的船顶上都站着船工在大声发出警示，以防这艘客船的船头或船尾在调整方向时会意外撞上来，这这种吃水量的两艘船一旦撞在一起，后果将不堪设想。

traits.value: Light blue color matching short sleeves

name: The House Pole-Carrying Servant
description: A servant who carried his luggage on a pole and followed his master of the scribe. Because the scribe was saying goodbye to his master, he also had to slacken off, secretly put his heavy luggage on the ground, and then looked back to see the priest who killed the sheep. on site.

chinese.name: 挑担家仆
chinese.description: 一位用扁担挑着行李，跟随着自己文士主人的仆人，因为文士在与主人家依依惜别，因此他也得了空档偷懒，偷偷将沉重的行李放在地上，而后回头去看杀羊祭祀的现场。

name: The Palanquin-Carrier of The Civil Official
description: On the bridge, the sedan-servant and the horse-riding military officer did not give way to each other. Under their sign, the bearers and horsemen on both sides relied on their masters, making noisiness. Humility is a fine culture that has existed since ancient times, but at that time, most people I have forgotten all this, just thinking about getting ahead and stepping on others.

chinese.name: 文官轿夫
chinese.description: 桥上坐轿文官和骑马武官互不相让，在他们的示意下，两边的轿夫与马夫各仗其主，吵闹不休，谦卑是自古以来便存在的优良文化，但在那时，大多数人都忘记了这些，只想着出人头地，把别人踩在脚下。

name: The Hotel Waiter
description: The guy at the foot shop is soliciting customers. He doesn’t know if he wants to be free or busy. Although the turnover of this hotel is not directly related to his wages, if the harvest is too bad, he may also be. Be driven away.

chinese.name: 酒店小二
chinese.description: 脚店的伙计，正在招揽顾客，也不知道他希望自己闲一些，还是希望忙一些，虽然说这间酒店的营业额跟自己的工钱没有直接关系，但要是收成太差了，自己也有可能会被赶走的吧。

name: The Vegetable Farmer
description:
A vegetable farmer who is selling his own vegetables to customers is eloquent and eloquent.
"Coriander, spicy green peppers, green onions, baby celery, lentils, eggplants, cucumbers, winter melons, large sea stalks, radishes, carrots, flat radishes, sprouts of toon, garlic, good leeks! Lord, you want What can I do?"

chinese.name: 菜农
chinese.description:
一位正在向客人售卖自家菜的菜农，口若悬河，滔滔不绝。
“香菜、辣青椒、勾葱、嫩芹菜、扁豆、茄子、黄瓜、架冬瓜、卖大海茄、卖萝卜、胡萝卜、扁萝卜、嫩芽的香椿、蒜儿来、好韭菜！这位爷您要来点什么？”

name: The Caravan Leader
description: A driver of a camel caravan. He led the camel to the forefront and mastered the direction of the caravan. He seemed to have been in this bustling and populous capital many times, and he could even calmly deal with all kinds of unexpected accidents on the road.

chinese.name: 骆驼队驭手
chinese.description: 一位骆驼商队的驭手。他牵着骆驼走在最前面，熟练地掌控着商队的走向，似是已经在这座繁华而人口众多的京城往来多次，甚至可以淡然应对路上出现的各种突发事故。

name: The Child-Holding Woman
description: A woman who is walking with her child on the street may be waiting for her family, or just holding her child out to see the scenery, so that he can also feel this leisurely and prosperous Bianjing.

chinese.name: 带娃妇人
chinese.description: 一位正在街边抱着孩子散步的妇人，说不定是在等待自己家人，或是只是单纯地抱着小孩子出来看看风景，让他也感受一下这悠闲而繁华的汴京。

name: The Palanquin-Carrier of The Civil Official
description: On the bridge, the sedan-servant and the horse-riding military officer did not give way to each other. Under their sign, the bearers and horsemen on both sides relied on their masters, making noisiness. Humility is a fine culture that has existed since ancient times, but at that time, most people I have forgotten all this, just thinking about getting ahead and stepping on others.

chinese.name: 文官轿夫
chinese.description: 桥上坐轿文官和骑马武官互不相让，在他们的示意下，两边的轿夫与马夫各仗其主，吵闹不休，谦卑是自古以来便存在的优良文化，但在那时，大多数人都忘记了这些，只想着出人头地，把别人踩在脚下。

name: The Vendor
description:
A hawker holding a portable stand, looking around for a stall to support the stall.
"The wine-carrying carts are walking in a hurry. It's better to set up a stall in another place. It's not worth it to be knocked down.

chinese.name: 卖货小贩
chinese.description:
一位手持便携式支架，四处寻觅摊位以支起货摊的小贩。
“这运酒的车马走得真是急，还是换个地方摆摊得好，被撞倒可就不值当了。”

name: The Absent-Minded Pedestrian
description: A passing pedestrian who seemed to hesitate to think about his mind, didn’t even notice that his legs had led him behind the paper horse stall. It’s best to take a quick look at the road ahead, or take another two steps for fear of hitting him. The stall is on.

chinese.name: 走神行人
chinese.description: 一位似是踌躇不前思索心事的路过行人，甚至没发现自己的双腿将他带到了纸马摊子的后方，最好还是快快看一眼前路吧，不然再走两步怕是要撞在摊子上了。

name: The Barge Haulers
description: The direct responsibilities of the Hongqiao shipwreck accident are several trackers. As the power of the passenger ship, the rope is tied to the top of the mast. The trackers should have stopped in time and asked the shipmen to lower the mast, but he did not. When they reacted, it was already burning eyebrows. To the point.

chinese.name: 纤夫
chinese.description: 虹桥船难事故的直接责任者是几个纤夫，作为客船动力，纤绳一头系桅杆顶，纤夫们本应该适时止步，招呼船工放下桅杆，但他没有，等他们反应过来的时候，已经到了火烧眉毛的地步了。

name: The Caravan Leader
description: A driver of a camel caravan. He led the camel to the forefront and mastered the direction of the caravan. He seemed to have been in this bustling and populous capital many times, and he could even calmly deal with all kinds of unexpected accidents on the road.

chinese.name: 骆驼队驭手
chinese.description: 一位骆驼商队的驭手。他牵着骆驼走在最前面，熟练地掌控着商队的走向，似是已经在这座繁华而人口众多的京城往来多次，甚至可以淡然应对路上出现的各种突发事故。

name: Traveler B
description: Tourists traveling in twos and threes, they may come out for a walk or go shopping, but now they have a dispute over where to go next. One wants to go east and one wants to go west. , There is another person who wants to stay on the bridge.

chinese.name: 游客乙
chinese.description: 三三两两结伴同游的游客们，他们可能是出来散步的，也可能是出来购物的，但现在，他们为接下来往那边走发生了争执，一个人想要往东，一个人想要去西，还有一个人想要留在桥上。

name: Bystander D
description: When the shipwreck was about to happen, the spectators at the bridge head pointed, or exclaimed, enclosing the right side guardrail of the arch bridge, and several people tried to rescue them by crossing the railings. In fact, in this case, everyone is the same. In a panic, no one can tell whether they are helping or adding chaos.

chinese.name: 看客丁
chinese.description: 船难将发之时，桥头的看客或指指点点，或惊呼不已，把拱桥的右侧护栏围得水泄不通，有几个人越过栏杆企图施救，其实，这种情况下，所有人都是慌张的，他们是在帮忙，还是在添乱，没人分得清楚。

name: A Passer-By with a Burden
description:
A bearer who almost came across misfortune, dodges aside when he sees the drunk soldiers.
"Good guy, this car is really reckless. But if I also have a donkey cart, I don't have to carry this broken pole every day."

chinese.name: 挑担的路人
chinese.description:
一位差点路遇飞来横祸的挑担者，在看到醉醺醺的士卒时连忙躲闪到了一边。
“好家伙，这车可真莽撞。不过要是我也有辆驴车，就不用天天挑着这破扁担了。”

name: Idle Soldier A
description:
A group of soldiers on official business, but they are not mindful of their tasks, they just slouchy gathering outside the yamen, or sitting or lying down waiting for the officer to appear.
"Spring is sleepy and autumn is lacking, and summer is nap, and winter is March when I can't wake up. Every day is a good time to sleep."

chinese.name: 懒散士卒甲
chinese.description:
一群公务在身的士卒，但他们对于自己的任务并不上心，只是懒懒散散地聚在衙门外，或坐或躺地等待着长官出现。
“春困秋乏夏打盹，睡不醒的冬三月。每天都是睡觉的好时候。”
